problem: Write a C/C++ program to generate the Fibonacci series:
         a) Using iteration (without recursion)
         b) Using recursion

Answear:--
what is fiboncci searies?
=>The Fibonacci series is a sequence of numbers in which each number is the sum of the two preceding ones.It starts with 0 and 1.
ex: 0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, â€¦.

a) here the code:

code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int n, i;
    int first = 0, second = 1, next;

    printf("Enter the number of terms: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Fibonacci Series: ");

    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (i <= 1) {
            next = i;
        } else {
            next = first + second;
            first = second;
            second = next;
        }
        printf("%d ", next);
    }

    return 0;
}


b)here the code using recurtion:

code:
#include <stdio.h>

int fibonacci(int n) {
    if (n == 0) return 0;
    if (n == 1) return 1;
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
}

int main() {
    int n, i;

    printf("Enter the number of terms: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Fibonacci Series: ");
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        printf("%d ", fibonacci(i));
    }

    return 0;
}


